quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  7,182,And those who cry lies to Our signs We will draw them on little by little whence they know not
  7,183,and I respite them -- assuredly My guile is sure
  7,184,Have they not reflected? No madness is in their comrade; he is naught but a plain warner
  7,185,"Or have they not considered the dominion of the heaven and of the earth, and what things God has created, and that it may be their term is already nigh? In what manner of discourse then will they after this believe"
  7,186,"Whomsoever God leads astray, no guide he has; He leaves them in their insolence blindly wandering"
  7,187,"They will question thee concerning the Hour, when it shall berth. Say: 'The knowledge of it is only with my Lord; none shall reveal it at its proper time, but He. Heavy is it in the heavens and the earth; it will not come on you but suddenly!' They will question thee, as though thou art well-informed of it. Say: 'The knowledge of it is only with God, but most men know not"
  7,188,"Say: 'I have no power to profit for myself; or hurt, but as God will. Had I knowledge of the Unseen I would have acquired much good, and evil would not have touched me. I am only a warner, and a bearer of good tidings, to a people believing"